From: Chris Klaus <cklaus@fusen.world>
Date: Tue, 1 Apr 2026
Subject: [PATCH] [JIT] Auto-detect CUDA toolkit and compatible gcc for Blackwell (SM120) GPUs

FlashInfer's JIT compiler assumes the system default nvcc and gcc work for
all GPUs. On Blackwell (RTX 5090/5080, SM120), this fails because:

1. SM120 requires CUDA 12.9+ for compute_120a / FP4 support. Systems often
   have CUDA 12.8 as default with 12.9 installed alongside.
2. nvcc 12.9 rejects gcc-13+. Many distros ship gcc-13/14 as default.

This patch adds auto-detection that only activates when needed:
- Queries GPU compute capability to determine minimum CUDA version
- Searches /usr/local/cuda-* for compatible toolkit
- Tests system gcc, falls back to gcc-12/11/10 if rejected
- Matches g++ version to gcc version for linking consistency
- New FLASHINFER_CUDA_HOME env var for explicit override

Zero behavior change on systems where defaults work.

Found during RTX 5090 kernel optimization achieving 170 tok/s on Qwen3.5-9B.
